Charlotte Maxeke hospital will shut down for seven days. More than 400 patients have had to be transferred after a fire at the facility on Friday. #DStv403​ #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Charlotte Maxeke hospital will shut down for seven days. More than 400 patients have had to be transferred after a fire at the facility on Friday. Gauteng Premier David Makhura is visiting the Charlotte Maxeke hospital in Johannesburg this morning to assess fire damage. Firefighters have been battling to contain a blaze that started yesterday and flared up again last night. Scores of patients are being moved to other facilities. Courtesy #DStv403 Gauteng Premier David Makhura, who visited the hospital, says the fire is not out, yet. READ: Firefighters battle blaze at Charlotte Maxeke hospital Firefighters battled through the night to contain a fire at the hospital. Structural engineers will conduct an assessment of the damage. Watch Gauteng Premier David Makhura address the media in the video above.